ArcFlow is an embedded graph database. Runs in-process — browser (WASM), Node.js, Python, Rust, native CLI. 5MB binary, no server. Try it: https://oz.com/engine

This repo (ozinc/arcflow) is the open-source MIT developer surface: SDK source (sdk/), React hooks (react/), MCP server (mcp/), examples (examples/), docs (docs/), install scripts (install/). The Core engine binary is closed source and fetched from GitHub Releases.

See AGENTS.md for the full public API and WorldCypher (ISO GQL) reference.
See CLAUDE.md for repo conventions and boundary rules.
